<subSubSection id="53E87EB1F54B1876FF65C8773E38FC35" pageId="3" pageNumber="1508" type="description">
<paragraph id="1B4D2D3AF54B1876FF65C8773E38FC35" blockId="3.[163,1071,701,1012]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1508">
N o t e s: 
<taxonomicName id="DCF256B9F54B1876FEDBC8773BB0FCE7" baseAuthorityName="PETROVITZ" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[285,424,785,806]" class="Insecta" family="Glaphyridae" genus="Eulasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="korbi">
<emphasis id="2986F128F54B1876FEDBC8773BB0FCE7" box="[285,424,785,806]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1508">Eulasia korbi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is likely to be a colour form of 
<taxonomicName id="DCF256B9F54B1876FD3DC87739DEFCE7" baseAuthorityName="FALDERMANN" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[763,966,785,806]" class="Insecta" family="Glaphyridae" genus="Eulasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysopyga">
<emphasis id="2986F128F54B1876FD3DC87739DEFCE7" box="[763,966,785,806]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1508">Eulasia chrysopyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as specimens with intermediate characters, or populations with not clear-cut conditions, are known. However, the two forms seems to occur mostly separately, therefore a subspecific rank may be possible. For example, among samples examined by us, all specimens from Köprüköy, Geyikli, exhibit almost completely white-yellowish long hair, departing significantly from the populations of ordinarily dark-haired 
<taxonomicName id="DCF256B9F54B1876FCDEC8C239B3FC78" baseAuthorityName="FALDERMANN" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[792,939,932,953]" class="Insecta" family="Glaphyridae" genus="Eulasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysopyga">
<emphasis id="2986F128F54B1876FCDEC8C239B3FC78" box="[792,939,932,953]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1508">E. chrysopyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
observed in most of the 
<collectingRegion id="D936E3D8F54B1876FEE6C8A73BDCFC16" box="[288,452,961,983]" country="Turkey" name="Erzurum" pageId="3" pageNumber="1508">Erzurum region</collectingRegion>
. A taxonomic re-evaluation of this taxon is anyway beyond the aim of this work, and we applied to our samples the current taxonomic arrangement.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
